		<h1>About Me&nbsp;</h1>
		<p>Since the early days of high school, I have had a fascination with graphic design. So much, in fact, that I started creating logos for the local robotics team, and various other small commissions. After I moved schools, I continued my work with graphics and help start a rookie robotics team. With this, I was slowly gaining more experience. As time went on, I went on to college to get my Bachelor's degree in Communication Technology. It was here where my career began to skyrocket.</p>
		<div class="portrait">
			<img src="Self Portrait.png" alt="Portrait">
		</div>
		<p>A major corporation started to notice my talent. I then started working for Caterpillar construction equipment as their own personal graphic designer. There I continued to work on making advertisements and training videos, as well as some other projects. Trust me, it stacks. Once a company knows what you are capable of, they'll never stop asking more from you. Just be sure you're getting paid well enough.</p>
